twist_adapters_231010.fasta
===========================

Twist Bioscience Universal Adapters (10 bp UDI) for PacBio, 800 records:
400 forward (72 nt) + 400 reverse (68 nt), interleaved as adjacent F/R pairs.

Source (public, no authentication):
  https://www.pacb.com/wp-content/uploads/Twist_Universal_Adapters_10bp_UDI_for_PacBio_10Oct2023.fasta_.zip
Also vendored by qiita-spots/qp-pacbio (BSD-3-Clause), which documents the same URL.

RECORD ORDER IS LOAD-BEARING. lima is invoked with `--neighbors`, which emits a
read only when its best-scoring barcode pair are ADJACENT RECORDS in this file.
Reordering the records changes which reads survive. Do not sort, dedup, or
regenerate this file; replace it wholesale and update the md5 pinned in the
control plane (`_LIMA_ADAPTER_SET_MD5`), which folds the adapter bytes into the
read-mask identity so a different adapter set re-mints rather than silently
reusing a mask built from other adapters.

The P5/P7 and TruSeq constant regions flanking each index are Illumina sequences.
Per Illumina document # 1000000002694 ("Illumina Adapter Sequences"), and
following the precedent of Trimmomatic's bundled adapter FASTAs:

  Oligonucleotide sequences (c) 2023 Illumina, Inc. All rights reserved.
